race.comment: XELCIMUS (8) has turned things around the prep and is bursting to win. Found one better for the third straight time last start when edged out over 1300m at this track. Maps beautifully from gate one so no excuses. SPANGLEDSTAR (7) returned from a 20-week spell and faced the starter for the 14th time when an eye-catching third over 1300m at this track last time out. Ran around three lengths slower than XELCIMUS on the same card but she does have greater scope for improvement. THE ROCKET (6) was unwanted in betting first-up at Ascot but flashed home late to grab third at the end of 1200m. Lightly raced three-year-old who will be tough to resist over the extra furlong today. TORA BORA (10) was runner-up here last time in the same race as SPANGLEDSTAR. Should be peaking at the third run back. PEMBETON (5) is back sharply in distance but cannot be ruled out.
